s of moderate volume, a phenomenon referred to as\nhomogeneous nucleation.\n  Since Kawasaki dynamics is conservative, i.e., particles are preserved, we\nneed to control non-local effects in the way droplets are formed and dissolved.\nThis is done via a deductive approach: the tube of typical trajectories leading\nto nucleation is described via a series of events on which the evolution of the\ngas consists of droplets wandering around on multiple space-time scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Apr 2023 11:22:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-28"}
