scopic analyses of the same data\nset, most notably from silicon in over-dense clumps in the wind. In the silicon\nline region, the variability power is redistributed towards lower frequencies,\nhinting at increased line variability in large clumps. In prospect of the\nmicrocalorimetry missions that are scheduled to launch within the next decade,\nexcess variance spectra present a promising approach to constrain the wind\nstructure.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Apr 2023 14:07:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-28"}
